    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b12-13_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">12</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        702 Sharp Building
                        18 East 11th St.
                        <del>,</del><add>K</add>ansas City 6, Mo.
                
                        July 11, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route #7,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Friend:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I read in the <hi rend="caps">KANSAS CITY STAR</hi> last night that the University of Missouri would offer your Epic America course as a live television broadcast beginning September 18 through January 22.</p>
                
                <p>I think this is just grand and I am happy indeed for you and Mrs. Neihardt. It will enable many people to participate who otherwise would never have the chance.</p>
                
                <p>I hope I shall be able to arrange to be in Columbia on or about Sept. 18th.</p>
                
                <p>Epic America has more meaning to me as I grow in experience and understanding.</p>
                
                <p>All good wishes to you and Mrs. Neihardt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Your friend,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Thomas W. Wright</signed>
                
                    <signed>Thomas W. Wright</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
